<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 7:48PM MDT  by NWS Albuquerque</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT PORTIONS OF EAST CENTRAL
ROOSEVELT AND SOUTHEASTERN CURRY COUNTIES THROUGH 815 PM MDT...
At 747 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Portales, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Portales.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If threatening weather approaches your area, take shelter in a sturdy
building.</instruction>
